rComments: He is a good prof but very boring. He used a Siri or google voice over for his videos which is a bit pointless, I just read them myself instead. He is nice and answers emails but monotone and boring in class.

His voice. Is. So. Monotonous. Honestly dont show up to class, youll fall asleep, unless you have questions. Hes super sweet and properly answers questions, its just that his classes are so unbearably boring its sad. Self learning is the way to go, memorize all of his resources and youll be fine. Very caring though, it must be the old age.

provides you with all the information (read the extra pdf he gives). tests was the usual difficulty, there's just lots of content so study early. However, he had the google voice-over person read slides for him cause I guess he just couldn't be bothered to read/explain himself. Monotone

Ok seriously, prof Lemaire puts everything you need (information wise) in his pdfs on the bottom of his slides. I never went to a single zoom course neither did I watch a video and thought his exams were actually quite easy just having read the slides and additional information at the bottom. Also, the quizzes are harder than the exams.

This is the second time I've had Lemaire. He's not the most interesting prof to listen to, but he basically reads off the slides so most students don't attend class. Only about 25 students out of nearly 200 were attending class by the end of the semester. His exams were really fair. There were 2 midterms, a dissertation, 5 quizzes, and a final.

At times I thought he was dead because he's so monotonous. But he is very sweet and caring. He answers everyone's questions no matter how stupid and repetitive they are. His questions on the exam were easy and reflected the material.

Not very interesting prof. Not bad but the content of the class is very difficult and the prof is kind of boring..... Fell asleep a couple times during lectures. At least he screenshares and you can follow along to the powerpoints on Zoom.
Honnetement le meilleur prof!! Je l'adore!
caring, repeats himself and gives a lot of information. he truly deserves more recognition than he now does here

He's a bit monotone and reads off the slides (so it's not the worst if you miss lectures). However, I find his exams to be easier than most ANP profs. There were 2 midterms (25% each), 5 quizzes and 1 assignment (10%), and a final exam (40%). He also records his lectures! Be sure to do the online quizzes before the exams (questions are repeated)!

Lemaire is an alright prof. I think he's really sweet and funny. All the information you need is on the powerpoint, but he does basically just read off them. This is good since missing his classes aren't the end of the world especially considering he records them. Plus, his exam questions are pretty straightforward and easier than the other profs.
He's boring and talks really slow like a priest
B-O-R-I-N-G
Le meilleur prof de ANP que tu peut avoir

Understanding and kind. Reads off the ppt, but that makes it easy since you don't need to show up to class. Doesn't put many trick questions in his exams. Just memorize the ppts and you'll get a good grade.

The material itself for this class was easy because you just need to study the slides and what's underneath them. As a lecturer, Dr. Lemaire seems a bit shy and reads off the slides a lot. Attendance is not mandatory since he records his lectures, but students should be fine studying the material itself without any guidance.

He does read right off the slides, which makes it easy if you don't want to go to class just read the lecs off brightsapce. He doesn't get the best rep for his teaching skills but he really does care about his students and understands this is a really hard class. Deserves more credit then he gets honestly.
He knows what he's talking about and gives you more than enough to succeed in his class. He's very nice and pretty funny. He truly deserves more credit than he gets on here.

Try to avoid Dr. Lemaire as a professor if you can. If you enjoy watching someone read an anatomy textbook (while never making eye-contact) to you as if it's their first time learning this material, this course is perfect for you. It's a tough course, so if you do get stuck with him, do your readings ahead of time.

Lemaire is an awesome prof, most people don't like the fact he reads his slides, word for word in the lectures. But in reality that's a bonus, since you don't have to show up to class! Just read his powerpoints, and the textbook and you'll be golden. He also gives practice tests with exact questions that will be on the midterms!

He was not the best prof for this course. He is boring, copies everything out of the textbook and is still lost, he is not clear when he speaks and has no idea what's going on. He has an accent that is very hard to understand which makes it even worse with his inability to teach.. READ THE TEXTBOOK! I would try to avoid him if you could.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Dr. Lemaire read off the slides the majority of the time, which was not helpful to students trying to stay awake during an 8:30 lecture. Although most of the questions on his midterm were expected, some were not on the slides in his Power Point presentations, so reading the textbook is necessary.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Most boring prof ever. He basically just reads his slides, I've never seen anything like it. To make us believe that he's actually teaching, he's gonna repeat what he just read out loud about 3 times using different words and formulations. Come on.
Most boring teacher ever, read directly off the slides and would stop mid sentence to change the page and continue reading off it. Almost don't have to go to class but study and you'll pass.
Records his classes and puts them on blackboard so attendance isn't mandatory. Usually reads but you can tell he's passionate about the information.

Extremely boring in class BUT he records his classes and posts them on Blackboard so you don't have to go to the actual class. Mid-term was hard but the final was much easier. I would recommend choosing Désilets if you have the choice. Also, he's unable to answer student's questions in class.
Really nice professor, mistakes in notes, easy A+

Some of his questions are so hard to answer correctly. I miss Desilet. Beware, this class is not impossible but much harder than anatomies with Desilet because his notes are scattered, and sometimes flawed too! Nice prof though.

Plus difficile que les deux autres ANP. Le professeur n'est pas stimulant, ses notes de cours sont assez compliquées à comprendre, et contiennent souvent des erreurs; le livre est donc la chose qui m'a sauvé. Les examen ont aussi des questions assez pointues et difficiles. J'aime bien ce cours mais j'ai dû y mettre 2  plus de travail que ANP1 et 2.

Yeah class can be very long because he is monotone, but his powerpoints are very clear. All the information you need to study is there. He also puts audios of the class on blackboard so you don't  even need to go to class.

HE IS BORING. He stands in front of the class in the same spot for the complete hour, doesn't move, and literally reads his slides word for word, and then he reads it again a second time and then maybe a third time. If you see Simon Lemaire on your schedule, CHANGE CLASSES I SWEAR
Don't go to class. Read his notes, do the practice exams. Class is 90% sleeping students and 10% students asking questions he usually needs a whole week to answer.
He is ok. He wasn't as enthusiastic as Professor Désilet but his power points are very well built and knows his anatomy.
Excellent prof qui est dédié à la réussite de ses étudiants, tout le matériel est accessible sur Campus Virtuel (Blackboard)!  Je prendrais d'autre cours avec ce prof!

A sweet person but boring prof. Extremely monotonous, stays in his corner during the entire lecture and simply reads his notes out loud. Good thing is, he does provide you with everything you could possibly need on Blackboard, (ppts, practice midterms, class recordings, etc) so you can get away with skipping class!

He only taught my class for a little less than half the lessons. His midterm was extremely reasonable and easy. His lectures, on the other hand, were SO boring. He'd stand in the corner reading off the slides in a monotone voice. I didn't even go to class, all the info is on the slides. Super nice and easy-going, but VERY boring.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: He's boring! It's like he's asking me to fall asleep in his class. He just reads off his slides.

Sa classe est trop ennuyante au point que quand je regarde derriere moi , je trouve pas mal de gens entrain de dormir. Il bouge pas de son coin, et sa facon de parler donne envie de dormir, il me fait regretter le fait de venir en classe!
Read from notes for entire class, tends to get confused and lost in what he's saying. Very monotonous
Longest classes; monotone and reads off the slides
Lemaire est un bon prof pas mal chill et ces tests ne sont pas trop difficiles mais demande quand même assez d'étude car il y a une montagne de ppt BONNE CHANCE À TOUS :)

Very nice prof. He is monotonous but for some reason it made the course a little easier to pass than the two other ANP courses as his expectations are very clear. Go to class, he can be pretty funny too!

He is a very sweet man. His voice is monotone and he basically just reads through the slides so the attendance isn`t manditory. However, he will crack a few jokes sometimes, and he is always there to help. You really need to study for his exams, but they're overall fair. Do recommend!

Very nice man, can surprise you sometimes with his funny comments however, he is boring most of the time. The class is very easy if you study and in general everyone did better than they did in anatomy 1505 and 1506. Also, the material itself is interesting and practical

He is RLY boring so monotone. The only good thing is that his midterms and exams are fairly easy you still have to study obviously its anatomy but easier than anp 05 - 06 and tells you what he wants you to know for the exams. His slides are short and clear so attendance isn't mandatory but he isn't very available out of class, its before or after
